# Check CHANGELOG First

Before doing any task in this repository, read `CHANGELOG.md` first and use it to understand recent work, release history, UI/theme decisions, and branch context.

This is mandatory before:

- editing code, configs, docs, or release files;
- building release artifacts or copying built frontend assets;
- committing, tagging, pushing, or creating PRs;
- diagnosing regressions, especially UI/theme/layout changes.

When work touches the frontend or release packaging, compare the current branch against the history recorded in `CHANGELOG.md` so previously shipped UI skin, liquid glass styling, responsive shell, and window/layout adjustments are not accidentally dropped.

